<li id="s4165" data-link-target="s4165" data-id="section/4165" style="list-style-type: '45. '">Kakwa</li><!--Section: section/4167, type: list-->
<li id="s4167" data-link-target="s4167" data-id="section/4167" style="list-style-type: '46. '">Karimojong</li><!--Section: section/4169, type: list-->
<li id="s4169" data-link-target="s4169" data-id="section/4169" style="list-style-type: '47. '">Kebu (Okebu)</li><!--Section: section/4171, type: list-->
<li id="s4171" data-link-target="s4171" data-id="section/4171" style="list-style-type: '48. '">Kuku</li><!--Section: section/4173, type: list-->
<li id="s4173" data-link-target="s4173" data-id="section/4173" style="list-style-type: '49. '">Kumam</li><!--Section: section/4175, type: list-->
<li id="s4175" data-link-target="s4175" data-id="section/4175" style="list-style-type: '50. '">Langi</li><!--Section: section/4177, type: list-->
<li id="s4177" data-link-target="s4177" data-id="section/4177" style="list-style-type: '51. '">Lendu</li><!--Section: section/4179, type: list-->
<li id="s4179" data-link-target="s4179" data-id="section/4179" style="list-style-type: '52. '">Lugbara</li><!--Section: section/4181, type: list-->
<li id="s4181" data-link-target="s4181" data-id="section/4181" style="list-style-type: '53. '">Madi</li><!--Section: section/4183, type: list-->
<li id="s4183" data-link-target="s4183" data-id="section/4183" style="list-style-type: '54. '">Mening</li><!--Section: section/4185, type: list-->
<li id="s4185" data-link-target="s4185" data-id="section/4185" style="list-style-type: '55. '">Mvuba</li><!--Section: section/4187, type: list-->
<li id="s4187" data-link-target="s4187" data-id="section/4187" style="list-style-type: '56. '">Napore</li><!--Section: section/4189, type: list-->
<li id="s4189" data-link-target="s4189" data-id="section/4189" style="list-style-type: '57. '">Ngikutio</li><!--Section: section/4191, type: list-->
<li id="s4191" data-link-target="s4191" data-id="section/4191" style="list-style-type: '58. '">Nubi</li><!--Section: section/4193, type: list-->
<li id="s4193" data-link-target="s4193" data-id="section/4193" style="list-style-type: '59. '">Nyangia</li><!--Section: section/4195, type: list-->
<li id="s4195" data-link-target="s4195" data-id="section/4195" style="list-style-type: '60. '">Pokot</li><!--Section: section/4197, type: list-->
<li id="s4197" data-link-target="s4197" data-id="section/4197" style="list-style-type: '61. '">Reli</li><!--Section: section/4199, type: list-->
<li id="s4199" data-link-target="s4199" data-id="section/4199" style="list-style-type: '62. '">Sabiny</li><!--Section: section/4201, type: list-->
<li id="s4201" data-link-target="s4201" data-id="section/4201" style="list-style-type: '63. '">Shana</li><!--Section: section/4203, type: list-->
<li id="s4203" data-link-target="s4203" data-id="section/4203" style="list-style-type: '64. '">So (Tepeth)</li><!--Section: section/4205, type: list-->
<li id="s4205" data-link-target="s4205" data-id="section/4205" style="list-style-type: '65. '">Vonoma</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/4207, type: title-->
<div id="s4207" data-link-target="s4207" data-id="section/4207" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="god">God or other deities</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="oath">Oaths to abide by constitution</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-0">FOURTH SCHEDULE. OATHS (Articles 15, 81, 82, 98, 108, 109, 111, 115, 149 and 256)</h3><!--Section: section/4208, type: body-->
<div id="s4208" data-link-target="s4208" data-id="section/4208" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">OATH OF ALLEGIANCE</p></div><!--Section: section/4209, type: body-->
<div id="s4209" data-link-target="s4209" data-id="section/4209" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">&#x27;I................................................................swear in the name of the Almighty God/ solemnly affirm that I will be faithful and bear true allegiance to the Republic of Uganda and that I will preserve, protect and defend the Constitution. [So help me God.]</p></div><!--Section: section/4210, type: body-->
<div id="s4210" data-link-target="s4210" data-id="section/4210" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">OATH OF PRESIDENT/VICE PRESIDENT</p></div><!--Section: section/4211, type: body-->
<div id="s4211" data-link-target="s4211" data-id="section/4211" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">&#x27;I................................................................swear in the name of the Almighty God/solemnly affirm/that I shall faithfully exercise the functions of the President/Vice-President of Uganda and shall uphold, preserve, protect, and defend the Constitution and observe the laws of Uganda and that I shall promote the welfare of the people of Uganda [So help me God.]</p></div><!--Section: section/4212, type: body-->
<div id="s4212" data-link-target="s4212" data-id="section/4212" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">JUDICIAL OATH</p></div><!--Section: section/4213, type: body-->
<div id="s4213" data-link-target="s4213" data-id="section/4213" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">&#x27;I................................................................, swear in the name of the Almighty God/solemnly affirm that I will well and truly exercise the judicial functions entrusted to me and will do right to all manner of people in accordance with the Constitution of the Republic of Uganda as by law established and in accordance with the laws and usage of the Republic of Uganda without fear or favour, affection or ill-will. (So help me God).</p></div><!--Section: section/4214, type: body-->
<div id="s4214" data-link-target="s4214" data-id="section/4214" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">SPEAKER/DEPUTY SPEAKER&#x27;S OATH</p></div><!--Section: section/4215, type: body-->
<div id="s4215" data-link-target="s4215" data-id="section/4215" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">&#x27;I................................................................, swear in the name of the Almighty God/solemnly affirm that I will at all times well and truly serve the Republic of Uganda in the Office of Speaker/Deputy Speaker and that I will support and uphold the Constitution of the Republic of Uganda as by law established. (So help me God).</p></div><!--Section: section/4216, type: body-->
<div id="s4216" data-link-target="s4216" data-id="section/4216" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">OATH OF PRIME MINISTER</p></div><!--Section: section/4217, type: body-->
<div id="s4217" data-link-target="s4217" data-id="section/4217" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">&#x27;I................................................................being appointed Prime Minister of Uganda swear in the name of the Almighty God/solemnly affirm that I will at all times well and truly serve the Republic of Uganda in the office of Prime Minister, and I will support and uphold the Constitution of the Republic of Uganda as by law established; and that I will to the best of my judgment at all times when required, freely give my counsel and advice to the President of Uganda and his/her successors in office as by law established for the good management of the public affairs of the Republic of Uganda; and that I will not directly or indirectly reveal any matter as shall come to my knowledge in the discharge of my duties and committed to my secrecy. (So help me God).</p></div><!--Section: section/4218, type: body-->
<div id="s4218" data-link-target="s4218" data-id="section/4218" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">OATH OF MINISTER</p></div><!--Section: section/4219, type: body-->
<div id="s4219" data-link-target="s4219" data-id="section/4219" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">&#x27;I................................................................being appointed a Minister of Uganda swear in the name of the Almighty God/solemnly affirm that I will at all times well and truly serve the Republic of Uganda in the office of a Minister; and that I will support and uphold the Constitution of the Republic of Uganda as by law established; and that I will to the best of my judgment at all times when required, freely give my counsel and advice to the President of Uganda and his/her successors in office as by law established for the good management of the public affairs of the Republic of Uganda; and that I will not directly or indirectly reveal any matter as shall come to my knowledge in the discharge of my duties and committed to my secrecy. [So help me God].</p></div><!--Section: section/4220, type: body-->
<div id="s4220" data-link-target="s4220" data-id="section/4220" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">OATH OF MEMBER OF PARLIAMENT</p></div><!--Section: section/4221, type: body-->
<div id="s4221" data-link-target="s4221" data-id="section/4221" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">&#x27;I................................................................, swear in the name of the Almighty God/solemnly affirm that I will give faithful service to this Parliament and support and uphold the Constitution of the Republic of Uganda as by law established. (So help me God.)</p></div><!--Section: section/4222, type: body-->
<div id="s4222" data-link-target="s4222" data-id="section/4222" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">OATH OF SECRETARY TO THE CABINET</p></div><!--Section: section/4223, type: body-->
<div id="s4223" data-link-target="s4223" data-id="section/4223" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">&#x27;I................................................................, being called upon to exercise the functions of Secretary to the Cabinet of Uganda swear in the name of the Almighty God/solemnly affirm that I will not directly or indirectly reveal such matters as shall be debated by the Cabinet and committed to my secrecy. (So help me God).</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/4224, type: title-->
<div id="s4224" data-link-target="s4224" data-id="section/4224" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">FIFTH SCHEDULE. REGIONAL GOVERNMENTS (Article 178)</h3><!--Section: section/4225, type: title-->
<div id="s4225" data-link-target="s4225" data-id="section/4225" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">1. Name of regional governments</h3><!--Section: section/4226, type: body-->
<div id="s4226" data-link-target="s4226" data-id="section/4226" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">A regional government may adopt its own name.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/4227, type: title-->
<div id="s4227" data-link-target="s4227" data-id="section/4227" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">2. Composition of Regional Assembly</h3><!--Section: section/4228, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4228" data-link-target="s4228" data-id="section/4228" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The composition of a regional assembly shall be prescribed by Act of Parliament and shall consist of-<!--Section: section/4230, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4230" data-link-target="s4230" data-id="section/4230" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="voteun">Claim of universal suffrage</span>
</div>directly elected representatives elected on the basis of universal adult suffrage at elections conducted by the Electoral Commission;</li><!--Section: section/4232, type: list-->
<li id="s4232" data-link-target="s4232" data-id="section/4232" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">representatives of women, who shall not be less than one third of the membership;</li><!--Section: section/4234, type: list-->
<li id="s4234" data-link-target="s4234" data-id="section/4234" style="list-style-type: 'c. '">representatives of the youth and persons with disabilities;</li><!--Section: section/4236, type: list-->
<li id="s4236" data-link-target="s4236" data-id="section/4236" style="list-style-type: 'd. '">representatives of indigenous cultural interests in areas where there is a traditional or cultural leader, nominated by the traditional or cultural leader but not exceeding fifteen per cent of the members of the regional assembly;</li><!--Section: section/4238, type: list-->
<li id="s4238" data-link-target="s4238" data-id="section/4238" style="list-style-type: 'e. '">district chairpersons in the region who shall be ex-officio members with no right to vote.</li></ol></li><!--Section: section/4240, type: list-->
<li id="s4240" data-link-target="s4240" data-id="section/4240" style="list-style-type: '2. '">A regional assembly shall have a speaker elected by the regional assembly from among its members; but a person shall only be taken to have been elected if the votes cast in his or her favour are more than fifty percent of all the members of the regional assembly.</li><!--Section: section/4242, type: list-->
<li id="s4242" data-link-target="s4242" data-id="section/4242" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The speaker of the regional assembly shall, in relation to the regional assembly, perform similar functions to those of the Speaker of Parliament.</li><!--Section: section/4244, type: list-->
<li id="s4244" data-link-target="s4244" data-id="section/4244" style="list-style-type: '4. '">Members of regional assemblies shall serve for the same term as members of district councils.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/4246, type: title-->
<div id="s4246" data-link-target="s4246" data-id="section/4246" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">3. Committees of the Regional Assembly</h3><!--Section: section/4247, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4247" data-link-target="s4247" data-id="section/4247" style="list-style-type: '1. '">A regional assembly may establish standing and other committees or organs for the efficient discharge of its functions.</li><!--Section: section/4249, type: list-->
<li id="s4249" data-link-target="s4249" data-id="section/4249" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The representatives of cultural interests shall constitute the standing committee on cultural matters.</li><!--Section: section/4251, type: list-->
<li id="s4251" data-link-target="s4251" data-id="section/4251" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The standing committee on cultural matters shall have, as against the rest of the members of the regional assembly, exclusive jurisdiction on the cultural matters of the region.</li><!--Section: section/4253, type: list-->
<li id="s4253" data-link-target="s4253" data-id="section/4253" style="list-style-type: '4. '">In this paragraph &quot;cultural matters&quot; include the following-<!--Section: section/4255, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4255" data-link-target="s4255" data-id="section/4255" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">the choice and installation of a traditional leader or cultural leader;</li><!--Section: section/4257, type: list-->
<li id="s4257" data-link-target="s4257" data-id="section/4257" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">all traditional and cultural matters relating to the traditional or cultural leader and to the institutions of the traditional leader or cultural leader as well as royal members of the traditional leadership;</li><!--Section: section/4259, type: list-->
<li id="s4259" data-link-target="s4259" data-id="section/4259" style="list-style-type: 'c. '">the choice, appointment and succession to clan and sub-clan leadership;</li><!--Section: section/4261, type: list-->
<li id="s4261" data-link-target="s4261" data-id="section/4261" style="list-style-type: 'd. '">clan, traditional and customary matters;</li><!--Section: section/4263, type: list-->
<li id="s4263" data-link-target="s4263" data-id="section/4263" style="list-style-type: 'e. '">matters relating to cultural funeral rites, cultural succession and customary heirs;</li><!--Section: section/4265, type: list-->
<li id="s4265" data-link-target="s4265" data-id="section/4265" style="list-style-type: 'f. '">cultural or traditional lands, sites, shrines and installations;</li><!--Section: section/4267, type: list-->
<li id="s4267" data-link-target="s4267" data-id="section/4267" style="list-style-type: 'g. '">clan lands, sites, shrines and installation; and</li><!--Section: section/4269, type: list-->
<li id="s4269" data-link-target="s4269" data-id="section/4269" style="list-style-type: 'h. '">traditional, customary and cultural practices which are consistent with this Constitution.</li></ol></li><!--Section: section/4271, type: list-->
<li id="s4271" data-link-target="s4271" data-id="section/4271" style="list-style-type: '5. '">In carrying out its responsibilities under subparagraphs (3) and (4), the standing committee on cultural matters shall consult the traditional or cultural leader of the region as well as the relevant clan leaders.</li><!--Section: section/4273, type: list-->
<li id="s4273" data-link-target="s4273" data-id="section/4273" style="list-style-type: '6. '">A decision of the standing committee on cultural matters shall not be effective until the decision has been approved by the traditional or cultural leader of the region and, in the case of succession under subparagraph (4)(a), by the clan or cultural leader&#x27;s council.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/4275, type: title-->
<div id="s4275" data-link-target="s4275" data-id="section/4275" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">4. Regional Government</h3><!--Section: section/4276, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4276" data-link-target="s4276" data-id="section/4276" style="list-style-type: '1. '">A regional government shall be led by a regional chairperson elected in accordance with this paragraph.</li><!--Section: section/4278, type: list-->
<li id="s4278" data-link-target="s4278" data-id="section/4278" style="list-style-type: '2. '">A person shall not be qualified to be elected a regional chairperson unless-<!--Section: section/4280, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4280" data-link-target="s4280" data-id="section/4280" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">he or she is a citizen of Uganda by birth as defined in article 10 of this Constitution and one of whose parents or grandparents is or was resident in the region and a member of the indigenous communities existing and residing within the borders of the region as at the first day of February, 1926;</li><!--Section: section/4282, type: list-->
<li id="s4282" data-link-target="s4282" data-id="section/4282" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">he or she is qualified to be a member of Parliament; and</li><!--Section: section/4284, type: list-->
<li id="s4284" data-link-target="s4284" data-id="section/4284" style="list-style-type: 'c. '">he or she is not less than thirty-five years of age.</li></ol></li><!--Section: section/4286, type: list-->
<li id="s4286" data-link-target="s4286" data-id="section/4286" style="list-style-type: '3. '">A regional chairperson shall-<!--Section: section/4288, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4288" data-link-target="s4288" data-id="section/4288" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">be directly elected by universal adult suffrage at an election conducted by the Electoral Commission;</li><!--Section: section/4290, type: list-->
<li id="s4290" data-link-target="s4290" data-id="section/4290" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">be willing and able, where applicable, to adhere to and perform the cultural and traditional functions and rites required by his or her office;</li><!--Section: section/4292, type: list-->
<li id="s4292" data-link-target="s4292" data-id="section/4292" style="list-style-type: 'c. '">where applicable, upon election, be given instruments of office by the cultural or traditional leader of the region; and</li><!--Section: section/4294, type: list-->
<li id="s4294" data-link-target="s4294" data-id="section/4294" style="list-style-type: 'd. '">be the political head of the regional government.</li></ol></li><!--Section: section/4296, type: list-->
<li id="s4296" data-link-target="s4296" data-id="section/4296" style="list-style-type: '4. '">Parliament shall by law prescribe the grounds and procedure for removal of the chairperson of the regional government.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/4298, type: title-->
<div id="s4298" data-link-target="s4298" data-id="section/4298" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">5. Ministers of Regional Government</h3><!--Section: section/4299, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4299" data-link-target="s4299" data-id="section/4299" style="list-style-type: '1. '">A regional government shall have regional ministers who shall be appointed by the head of the regional government with the approval of the regional assembly.</li><!--Section: section/4301, type: list-->
<li id="s4301" data-link-target="s4301" data-id="section/4301" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The number of regional ministers of a region shall be determined by Parliament.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/4303, type: title-->
<div id="s4303" data-link-target="s4303" data-id="section/4303" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">6. Cooperation with Central Government</h3><!--Section: section/4304, type: body-->
<div id="s4304" data-link-target="s4304" data-id="section/4304" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">A regional government shall cooperate with the Ministries of the Central Government but on policy matters they shall liaise with the office of the President.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/4305, type: title-->
<div id="s4305" data-link-target="s4305" data-id="section/4305" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">7. Voting in the Regional Assembly</h3><!--Section: section/4306, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4306" data-link-target="s4306" data-id="section/4306" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Representatives of cultural interests as defined in paragraph 3 shall not vote on any partisan matter.</li><!--Section: section/4308, type: list-->
<li id="s4308" data-link-target="s4308" data-id="section/4308" style="list-style-type: '2. '">A matter shall be considered to be of a partisan nature if in the course of its being tabled or debated in a regional assembly it is declared by a majority vote of the directly elected representatives to be partisan.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/4310, type: title-->
<div id="s4310" data-link-target="s4310" data-id="section/4310" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">8. Role of traditional or cultural leader</h3><!--Section: section/4311, type: body-->
<div id="s4311" data-link-target="s4311" data-id="section/4311" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Where a traditional leader or cultural leader exists in a region the traditional or cultural leader shall-</p><!--Section: section/4312, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4312" data-link-target="s4312" data-id="section/4312" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">be the titular head of the regional government;</li><!--Section: section/4314, type: list-->
<li id="s4314" data-link-target="s4314" data-id="section/4314" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">be the titular head of the regional assembly and shall open, address and close the sessions of the regional assembly; and</li><!--Section: section/4316, type: list-->
<li id="s4316" data-link-target="s4316" data-id="section/4316" style="list-style-type: 'c. '">enjoy the benefits and privileges and roles as provided for in article 246 of this Constitution and by Parliament and the regional assembly.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/4318, type: title-->
<div id="s4318" data-link-target="s4318" data-id="section/4318" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">9. Functions and services of regional governments</h3><!--Section: section/4319, type: body-->
<div id="s4319" data-link-target="s4319" data-id="section/4319" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The functions and services for which a regional government is responsible are as follows-</p><!--Section: section/4320, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4320" data-link-target="s4320" data-id="section/4320" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">secondary education and tertiary institutions except national universities and other national institutions;</li><!--Section: section/4322, type: list-->
<li id="s4322" data-link-target="s4322" data-id="section/4322" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">regional roads;</li><!--Section: section/4324, type: list-->
<li id="s4324" data-link-target="s4324" data-id="section/4324" style="list-style-type: 'c. '">regional referral hospitals other than national referral hospitals and national medical institutions;</li><!--Section: section/4326, type: list-->
<li id="s4326" data-link-target="s4326" data-id="section/4326" style="list-style-type: 'd. '">co-ordination, monitoring and supervision of agriculture;</li><!--Section: section/4328, type: list-->
<li id="s4328" data-link-target="s4328" data-id="section/4328" style="list-style-type: 'e. '">forests, other than, forests, national parks and wildlife reserves managed by the Government;</li><!--Section: section/4330, type: list-->
<li id="s4330" data-link-target="s4330" data-id="section/4330" style="list-style-type: 'f. '">culture;</li><!--Section: section/4332, type: list-->
<li id="s4332" data-link-target="s4332" data-id="section/4332" style="list-style-type: 'g. '">cultural and traditional lands;</li><!--Section: section/4334, type: list-->
<li id="s4334" data-link-target="s4334" data-id="section/4334" style="list-style-type: 'h. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="langprot">Protection of language use</span>
</div>promotion of local languages, crafts and antiquities;</li><!--Section: section/4336, type: list-->
<li id="s4336" data-link-target="s4336" data-id="section/4336" style="list-style-type: 'i. '">water;</li><!--Section: section/4338, type: list-->
<li id="s4338" data-link-target="s4338" data-id="section/4338" style="list-style-type: 'j. '">sanitation;</li><!--Section: section/4340, type: list-->
<li id="s4340" data-link-target="s4340" data-id="section/4340" style="list-style-type: 'k. '">to levy surcharge or cess subject to the approval of Central Government;</li><!--Section: section/4342, type: list-->
<li id="s4342" data-link-target="s4342" data-id="section/4342" style="list-style-type: 'l. '">functions and services surrendered voluntarily by a district council or district councils;</li><!--Section: section/4344, type: list-->
<li id="s4344" data-link-target="s4344" data-id="section/4344" style="list-style-type: 'm. '">receiving copies of financial accountability of districts to the Central Government to enable the regional government monitor and supervise the implementation of government programmes.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/4346, type: title-->
<div id="s4346" data-link-target="s4346" data-id="section/4346" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">10. Land</h3><!--Section: section/4347, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4347" data-link-target="s4347" data-id="section/4347" style="list-style-type: '1. '">A regional government may establish a regional land board whose functions may include the following-<!--Section: section/4349, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4349" data-link-target="s4349" data-id="section/4349" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">coordination and monitoring of land use in the region;</li><!--Section: section/4351, type: list-->
<li id="s4351" data-link-target="s4351" data-id="section/4351" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">planning of land use in the region; except that if there is a conflict between regional land planning and Central Government land planning, the latter shall prevail.</li></ol></li><!--Section: section/4353, type: list-->
<li id="s4353" data-link-target="s4353" data-id="section/4353" style="list-style-type: '2. '">A regional land board shall consist of-<!--Section: section/4355, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4355" data-link-target="s4355" data-id="section/4355" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">all chairpersons of the District Land Boards in the region;</li><!--Section: section/4357, type: list-->
<li id="s4357" data-link-target="s4357" data-id="section/4357" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">an equal number of members appointed by the regional government.</li></ol></li><!--Section: section/4359, type: list-->
<li id="s4359" data-link-target="s4359" data-id="section/4359" style="list-style-type: '3. '">A regional land board shall be represented on each District Land Board in its region in a manner prescribed by Parliament.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/4361, type: title-->
<div id="s4361" data-link-target="s4361" data-id="section/4361" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">11. Financial provisions for regional governments</h3><!--Section: section/4362, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4362" data-link-target="s4362" data-id="section/4362" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Where a regional government is established the government shall work out a formula of granting unconditional grants to the regional government having regard to the Seventh Schedule to this Constitution.</li><!--Section: section/4364, type: list-->
<li id="s4364" data-link-target="s4364" data-id="section/4364" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Experts under the general direction of Government and in consultation with regional governments shall work out the formula for the financial allocation to regional governments.</li><!--Section: section/4366, type: list-->
<li id="s4366" data-link-target="s4366" data-id="section/4366" style="list-style-type: '3. '">Grants sent to the region may change in light of economic and social conditions such as population and other similar considerations.</li><!--Section: section/4368, type: list-->
<li id="s4368" data-link-target="s4368" data-id="section/4368" style="list-style-type: '4. '">There shall also be a mechanism to resort to in case the central government without reasonable cause fails to remit funds to the regional government.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/4370, type: title-->
<div id="s4370" data-link-target="s4370" data-id="section/4370" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">12. Recognition of cultural diversity and equitable distribution of resources</h3><!--Section: section/4371, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4371" data-link-target="s4371" data-id="section/4371" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Each regional government must recognize and respect the different cultures existing within the region.</li><!--Section: section/4373, type: list-->
<li id="s4373" data-link-target="s4373" data-id="section/4373" style="list-style-type: '2. '">A regional government shall ensure that there is equitable distribution of the resources in the region in accordance with a formula worked out by Government in consultation with regional governments.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/4375, type: title-->
<div id="s4375" data-link-target="s4375" data-id="section/4375" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">13. National Cultural Heritage Sites</h3><!--Section: section/4376, type: body-->
<div id="s4376" data-link-target="s4376" data-id="section/4376" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Parliament shall by law-</p><!--Section: section/4377, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4377" data-link-target="s4377" data-id="section/4377" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">gazette national cultural heritage sites; and</li><!--Section: section/4379, type: list-->
<li id="s4379" data-link-target="s4379" data-id="section/4379" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">provide for the ownership and management of the cultural sites referred to in subparagraph (a) of this paragraph.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/4381, type: title-->
<div id="s4381" data-link-target="s4381" data-id="section/4381" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">14. Take-over of regional government by President</h3><!--Section: section/4382, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4382" data-link-target="s4382" data-id="section/4382" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Where-<!--Section: section/4384, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4384" data-link-target="s4384" data-id="section/4384" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">the High Court determines that there is failure to comply with the requirements of paragraph 12;</li><!--Section: section/4386, type: list-->
<li id="s4386" data-link-target="s4386" data-id="section/4386" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">the regional government so requests and it is in the public interest to do so;</li><!--Section: section/4388, type: list-->
<li id="s4388" data-link-target="s4388" data-id="section/4388" style="list-style-type: 'c. '">a state of emergency has been declared in the region or in Uganda generally; or</li><!--Section: section/4390, type: list-->
<li id="s4390" data-link-target="s4390" data-id="section/4390" style="list-style-type: 'd. '">it has become extremely difficult or impossible for the regional government to function;</li></ol><!--Section: section/4392, type: body-->
<div id="s4392" data-link-target="s4392" data-id="section/4392" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">a regional government shall be liable to a take-over of its administration by the President in a manner prescribed by an Act of Parliament and similar to the take-over of administration of a district under article 202 of this Constitution.</p></div>
</li><!--Section: section/4393, type: list-->
<li id="s4393" data-link-target="s4393" data-id="section/4393" style="list-style-type: '2. '">In the circumstances described in subparagraph (1), the President may, with the approval of two thirds of the members of Parliament, assume the executive and legislative powers of the regional government.</li><!--Section: section/4395, type: list-->
<li id="s4395" data-link-target="s4395" data-id="section/4395" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The exercise by the President of the power to assume the executive and legislative powers in subparagraph (2), may be done through such persons or officers as the President may appoint; and the legislative functions shall be exercised by making statutory instruments.</li><!--Section: section/4397, type: list-->
<li id="s4397" data-link-target="s4397" data-id="section/4397" style="list-style-type: '4. '">Where the President assumes the exercise of the legislative powers of a regional government under this paragraph, the President shall have no power to make laws on cultural matters as defined in paragraph 3 of this Schedule.</li><!--Section: section/4399, type: list-->
<li id="s4399" data-link-target="s4399" data-id="section/4399" style="list-style-type: '5. '">Unless approved by Parliament for a longer term, the exercise by the President of the power to take over, shall be for a period not exceeding ninety days.</li><!--Section: section/4401, type: list-->
<li id="s4401" data-link-target="s4401" data-id="section/4401" style="list-style-type: '6. '">Upon the expiry of the term under subparagraph (5)-<!--Section: section/4403, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4403" data-link-target="s4403" data-id="section/4403" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">the President shall hand back the administration of the region to the incumbent regional government; or</li><!--Section: section/4405, type: list-->
<li id="s4405" data-link-target="s4405" data-id="section/4405" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">if Parliament, by a resolution supported by not less than two thirds of all members of Parliament, decides that the prevailing circumstances still make it impossible for the incumbent regional government to resume the administration of the region-<!--Section: section/4407, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4407" data-link-target="s4407" data-id="section/4407" style="list-style-type: 'i. '">where the unexpired term of the regional assembly is longer than twelve months, the President shall cause elections to be held for a new regional assembly within sixty days; or</li><!--Section: section/4409, type: list-->
<li id="s4409" data-link-target="s4409" data-id="section/4409" style="list-style-type: 'ii. '">where the unexpired term of the regional assembly is less than twelve months the President shall continue to administer the region until the next elections are held.</li></ol></li></ol></li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/4411, type: title-->
<div id="s4411" data-link-target="s4411" data-id="section/4411" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">SIXTH SCHEDULE. FUNCTIONS AND SERVICES FOR WHICH GOVERNMENT IS RESPONSIBLE (Article 189)</h3><!--Section: section/4412, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s4412" data-link-target="s4412" data-id="section/4412" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Arms, ammunition and explosives.</li><!--Section: section/4414, type: list-->
<li id="s4414" data-link-target="s4414" data-id="section/4414" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Defence, security, maintenance of law and order.</li><!--Section: section/4416, type: list-->
<li id="s4416" data-link-target="s4416" data-id="section/4416" style="list-style-type: '3. '">Banks, banking, promissory notes, currency and exchange control.</li><!--Section: section/4418, type: list-->
<li id="s4418" data-link-target="s4418" data-id="section/4418" style="list-style-type: '4. '">Subject to this Constitution, taxation and taxation policy.</li><!--Section: section/4420, type: list-->
<li id="s4420" data-link-target="s4420" data-id="section/4420" style="list-style-type: '5. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="citdep">Power to deport citizens</span>
</div>Citizenship, immigration, emigration, refugees, deportation, extradition, passports and national identity cards.</li><!--Section: section/4422, type: list-->
<li id="s4422" data-link-target="s4422" data-id="section/4422" style="list-style-type: '6. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="intprop">Provisions for intellectual property</span>
</div>Copyrights, patents and trademarks and all forms of intellectual property, incorporation and regulation of business organisations.</li><!--Section: section/4424, type: list-->
<li id="s4424" data-link-target="s4424" data-id="section/4424" style="list-style-type: '7. '">Land, mines, mineral and water resources and the environment.</li><!--Section: section/4426, type: list-->
<li id="s4426" data-link-target="s4426" data-id="section/4426" style="list-style-type: '8. '">National parks, as may be prescribed by Parliament.</li><!--Section: section/4428, type: list-->
<li id="s4428" data-link-target="s4428" data-id="section/4428" style="list-style-type: '9. '">Public holidays.</li><!--Section: section/4430, type: list-->
<li id="s4430" data-link-target="s4430" data-id="section/4430" style="list-style-type: '10. '">National monuments, antiquities, archives and public records, as Parliament may determine.</li><!--Section: section/4432, type: list-->
<li id="s4432" data-link-target="s4432" data-id="section/4432" style="list-style-type: '11. '">Foreign relations and external trade.</li><!--Section: section/4434, type: list-->
<li id="s4434" data-link-target="s4434" data-id="section/4434" style="list-style-type: '12. '">The regulation of trade and commerce.</li><!--Section: section/4436, type: list-->
<li id="s4436" data-link-target="s4436" data-id="section/4436" style="list-style-type: '13. '">Making national plans for the provision of services and co-ordinating plans made by local governments.</li><!--Section: section/4438, type: list-->
<li id="s4438" data-link-target="s4438" data-id="section/4438" style="list-style-type: '14. '">National elections.</li><!--Section: section/4440, type: list-->
<li id="s4440" data-link-target="s4440" data-id="section/4440" style="list-style-type: '15. '">Energy policy.</li><!--Section: section/4442, type: list-->
<li id="s4442" data-link-target="s4442" data-id="section/4442" style="list-style-type: '16. '">Transport and communications policy.</li><!--Section: section/4444, type: list-->
<li id="s4444" data-link-target="s4444" data-id="section/4444" style="list-style-type: '16A. '">Development and upgrading of national roads.</li><!--Section: section/4446, type: list-->
<li id="s4446" data-link-target="s4446" data-id="section/4446" style="list-style-type: '17. '">National censuses and statistics.</li><!--Section: section/4448, type: list-->
<li id="s4448" data-link-target="s4448" data-id="section/4448" style="list-style-type: '18. '">Public services of Uganda.</li><!--Section: section/4450, type: list-->
<li id="s4450" data-link-target="s4450" data-id="section/4450" style="list-style-type: '19. '">The Judiciary.</li><!--Section: section/4452, type: list-->
<li id="s4452" data-link-target="s4452" data-id="section/4452" style="list-style-type: '20. '">National standards.</li><!--Section: section/4454, type: list-->
<li id="s4454" data-link-target="s4454" data-id="section/4454" style="list-style-type: '21. '">Education policy.</li><!--Section: section/4456, type: list-->
<li id="s4456" data-link-target="s4456" data-id="section/4456" style="list-style-type: '22. '">National surveys and mapping.</li><!--Section: section/4458, type: list-->
<li id="s4458" data-link-target="s4458" data-id="section/4458" style="list-style-type: '23. '">Industrial policy.</li><!--Section: section/4460, type: list-->
<li id="s4460" data-link-target="s4460" data-id="section/4460" style="list-style-type: '24. '">Forest and wildlife reserve policy and management.</li><!--Section: section/4462, type: list-->
<li id="s4462" data-link-target="s4462" data-id="section/4462" style="list-style-type: '25. '">National research policy.</li><!--Section: section/4464, type: list-->
<li id="s4464" data-link-target="s4464" data-id="section/4464" style="list-style-type: '26. '">Control and management of epidemics and disasters.</li><!--Section: section/4466, type: list-->
<li id="s4466" data-link-target="s4466" data-id="section/4466" style="list-style-type: '27. '">Health policy.</li><!--Section: section/4468, type: list-->
<li id="s4468" data-link-target="s4468" data-id="section/4468" style="list-style-type: '28. '">Agricultural policy.</li><!--Section: section/4470, type: list-->
<li id="s4470" data-link-target="s4470" data-id="section/4470" style="list-style-type: '29. '">Any matter incidental to or connected with the functions and services mentioned in this Schedule.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/4472, type: title-->
<div id="s4472" data-link-target="s4472" data-id="section/4472" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">SEVENTH SCHEDULE. UNCONDITIONAL GRANT TO LOCAL GOVERNMENTS (Article 193)</h3><!--Section: section/4473, type: body-->
<div id="s4473" data-link-target="s4473" data-id="section/4473" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">Unconditional grant is the minimum amount to be paid to the local governments to run the decentralised services. For a given fiscal year, this amount is equal to the amount paid to local governments in the preceding fiscal year for the same items adjusted[2] for general price changes plus or minus the budgeted cost of running added or subtracted services; calculated in accordance with the following formula-</p></div><!--Section: section/4474, type: body-->
<div id="s4474" data-link-target="s4474" data-id="section/4474" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">Y1 = Y0 + bY0 + X1</p></div><!--Section: section/4475, type: body-->
<div id="s4475" data-link-target="s4475" data-id="section/4475" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">= (1+b) Y0 + X1</p></div><!--Section: section/4476, type: body-->
<div id="s4476" data-link-target="s4476" data-id="section/4476" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">Where Y1 is the minimum unconditional grant for the current fiscal year;</p></div><!--Section: section/4477, type: body-->
<div id="s4477" data-link-target="s4477" data-id="section/4477" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">Y0 is the minimum unconditional grant in the preceding fiscal year;</p></div><!--Section: section/4478, type: body-->
<div id="s4478" data-link-target="s4478" data-id="section/4478" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">b is the percentage change if any, in the general price levels in the preceding fiscal year; and</p></div><!--Section: section/4479, type: body-->
<div id="s4479" data-link-target="s4479" data-id="section/4479" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">X1 is the net change in the budgeted cost of running added and subtracted services in the current year.</p></div><!--Section: section/4480, type: body-->
<div id="s4480" data-link-target="s4480" data-id="section/4480" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">For the purposes of this formula, the current fiscal year shall be taken to commence with fiscal year 1995/96.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

  </div>
